postcontent:
I am selling my custom Ruger MKIII .22 pistol. The original fluted steel barrel has been replaced with a light weight Tactical Solutions 4.5" threaded barrel with fiber optic front sight. I added a picatinny rail for an optic, like a Deltapoint. The original trigger kit has also been replaced with a match grade adjustable trigger kit that has a 3.5lb trigger pull. I also replaced the original Ruger grip plates with a very comfortable, rubber Hogue grip with finger grooves and thumb rest. Over $1000 invested!
I am including the original fluted barrel with weaver rail, the original trigger parts and the original Ruger grip plates. This particular Ruger is VERY difficult to find. This package comes with (2) 10rnd clips. I have more Ruger brand 10rnd clips if you're interested. The extra clips will cost $40 each. I do not have the original box but I will include a black zippered gun bag that holds the gun and parts. This gun is in amazing condition and is VERY accurate and fun to shoot! It's also a lot less expensive to shoot than other calibers. I usually shoot CCI Mini Mag 40 grain ammo but it will work with just about anything. It's a reliable Ruger! Contact me if interested and I'm open to serious cash "Best Offers". Buyer will need to sign a Firearm Bill of Sale and present their Texas Drivers License and/or CHL.NOTE: Because both barrels are included in this sale, you will esentially have 2 firearms. The barrels of Ruger .22 pistols are the serialized part, which the ATF considers "the gun".
